Document: CameraAttributesPractical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributespractical.rst
Summary: Provides practical camera attributes for real-time adjustments.

CameraAttributesPractical

Inherits: CameraAttributes < Resource

This class allows you to adjust camera attributes in real-time, overriding the default settings of a Camera3D or Camera2D. It's particularly useful for dynamic effects like depth of field, bloom, or color correction that need to be controlled during gameplay or through code.

Properties:
enabled (bool): If true, this CameraAttributes resource is active and its properties will be applied. Default: true.
Keep in mind that this property is often controlled externally by the Camera3D or Camera2D node itself, so manually changing it might not always have the desired effect if the camera is managing its attributes.

Keep in mind that this property is often controlled externally by the Camera3D or Camera2D node itself, so manually changing it might not always have the desired effect if the camera is managing its attributes.

Key Rule: The `enabled` property determines if the practical attributes are applied. If `false`, the camera will revert to its default settings or other active attributes.

