Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributespractical.rst
Summary: Provides a practical, easy-to-use interface for camera attributes, inheriting from CameraAttributes, Resource, RefCounted, and Object.

CameraAttributesPractical
Inherits: CameraAttributes < Resource < RefCounted < Object

Camera settings in an easy to use format.
---CHUNK---
Document: CameraAttributesPractical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributespractical.rst
Summary: Defines practical camera attributes like exposure and depth of field, explaining how they interact with WorldEnvironment and Camera3D nodes.
Controls camera-specific attributes such as auto-exposure, depth of field, and exposure override.

When used in a WorldEnvironment it provides default settings for exposure, auto-exposure, and depth of field that will be used by all cameras without their own CameraAttributes, including the editor camera. When used in a Camera3D it will override any CameraAttributes set in the WorldEnvironment. When used in VoxelGI or LightmapGI, only the exposure settings will be used.

Note: Depth of field blur is only supported in the Forward+ and Mobile rendering methods, not Compatibility.

Note: Auto-exposure is only supported in the Forward+ rendering method, not Mobile or Compatibility.
---CHUNK---
Document: CameraAttributesPractical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributespractical.rst
Summary: Defines practical camera attributes for depth of field and auto-exposure.

Properties:
* auto_exposure_max_sensitivity (float): The maximum sensitivity for auto-exposure. Default: 800.0
* auto_exposure_min_sensitivity (float): The minimum sensitivity for auto-exposure. Default: 0.0
* dof_blur_amount (float): Controls the intensity of the depth of field blur. Default: 0.1
* dof_blur_far_distance (float): The distance from the camera where the far blur effect begins to fade out. Default: 10.0
* dof_blur_far_enabled (bool): Enables or disables the far depth of field blur effect. Default: false
* dof_blur_far_transition (float): The transition range for the far depth of field blur. Default: 5.0
* dof_blur_near_distance (float): The distance from the camera where the near blur effect begins to fade out. Default: 2.0
* dof_blur_near_enabled (bool): Enables or disables the near depth of field blur effect. Default: false
* dof_blur_near_transition (float): The transition range for the near depth of field blur. Default: 1.0
---CHUNK---
Document: CameraAttributesPractical
Path: godot/classes/class_cameraattributespractical.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the CameraAttributesPractical class, which controls practical camera attributes like auto-exposure and depth of field blur.

Property Descriptions
auto_exposure_max_sensitivity (float): The maximum sensitivity (in ISO) used when calculating auto exposure. When calculating scene average luminance, color values will be clamped to at least this value. This limits the auto-exposure from exposing below a certain brightness, resulting in a cut off point where the scene will remain bright. Default: 800.0
Method: set_auto_exposure_max_sensitivity(value: float)
Method: get_auto_exposure_max_sensitivity() → float

auto_exposure_min_sensitivity (float): The minimum sensitivity (in ISO) used when calculating auto exposure. When calculating scene average luminance, color values will be clamped to at least this value. This limits the auto-exposure from exposing above a certain brightness, resulting in a cut off point where the scene will remain dark. Default: 0.0
Method: set_auto_exposure_min_sensitivity(value: float)
Method: get_auto_exposure_min_sensitivity() → float

dof_blur_amount (float): Sets the maximum amount of blur. When using physically-based blur amounts, will instead act as a multiplier. High values lead to an increased amount of blurriness, but can be much more expensive to calculate. It is best to keep this as low as possible for a given art style. Default: 0.1
Method: set_dof_blur_amount(value: float)
Method: get_dof_blur_amount() → float

dof_blur_far_distance (float): Objects further from the Camera3D by this amount will be blurred by the depth of field effect. Measured in meters. Default: 10.0
Method: set_dof_blur_far_distance(value: float)
Method: get_dof_blur_far_distance() → float

dof_blur_far_enabled (bool): Enables depth of field blur for objects further than dof_blur_far_distance. Strength of blur is controlled by dof_blur_amount and modulated by dof_blur_far_transition.
Note: Depth of field blur is only supported in the Forward+ and Mobile rendering methods, not Compatibility.
Note: Depth of field blur is not supported on viewports that have a transparent background (where Viewport.transparent_bg is true).
Default: false
Method: set_dof_blur_far_enabled(value: bool)
Method: is_dof_blur_far_enabled() → bool

dof_blur_far_transition (float): When positive, distance over which (starting from dof_blur_far_distance) blur effect will scale from 0 to dof_blur_amount. When negative, uses physically-based scaling so depth of field effect will scale from 0 at dof_blur_far_distance and will increase in a physically accurate way as objects get further from the Camera3D. Default: 5.0
Method: set_dof_blur_far_transition(value: float)
Method: get_dof_blur_far_transition() → float

dof_blur_near_distance (float): Objects closer from the Camera3D by this amount will be blurred by the depth of field effect. Measured in meters. Default: 2.0
Method: set_dof_blur_near_distance(value: float)
Method: get_dof_blur_near_distance() → float

dof_blur_near_enabled (bool): Enables depth of field blur for objects closer than dof_blur_near_distance. Strength of blur is controlled by dof_blur_amount and modulated by dof_blur_near_transition.
Note: Depth of field blur is only supported in the Forward+ and Mobile rendering methods, not Compatibility.
Note: Depth of field blur is not supported on viewports that have a transparent background (where Viewport.transparent_bg is true).
Default: false
Method: set_dof_blur_near_enabled(value: bool)
Method: is_dof_blur_near_enabled() → bool

dof_blur_near_transition (float): When positive, distance over which blur effect will scale from 0 to dof_blur_amount, ending at dof_blur_near_distance. When negative, uses physically-based scaling so depth of field effect will scale from 0 at dof_blur_near_distance and will increase in a physically accurate way as objects get closer to the Camera3D. Default: 1.0
Method: set_dof_blur_near_transition(value: float)
Method: get_dof_blur_near_transition() → float